Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%mins}. Break up the mince
as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}. Halve the
@Burger Buns{2}. Toast the buns in your #toaster{}.

Once the beef has browned, stir in the @Beef Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Water{50%milliliter}. Simmer, ~{1-2%mins}. Add a
splash of water if needed.

Meanwhile, in a #bowl{}, mix together the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%grams},
@Coleslaw Mix{120%grams}, @Cider Vinegar{15%milliliter} and the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}
and @Sugar{1/2%tsp}. Toss to coat.

Lay the toasted buns on #plates{}, cut-side up. Top with the beef mince,
cheese and @Burger Sauce{45%grams} - as much as you'd like. Sprinkle the
@Crispy Onions{1%sachet} over. Serve the salad on the side. Enjoy!